Problem Name: 2812. Find the Safest Path in a Grid


---

1. Problem Statement

You are given an n × n grid.

1 → Cell contains a thief.

0 → Empty cell.


You start from (0,0) and want to reach (n−1,n−1).

You may move only in 4 directions:

Up

Down

Left

Right


The safeness factor of a path is

> Minimum Manhattan distance between any cell on the path and the nearest thief.



Your task is to return the maximum possible safeness factor among all possible paths.


