9. Why This Works

Multi-Source BFS guarantees each cell gets the shortest distance to its nearest thief because BFS explores the grid level by level from all thieves simultaneously.

Binary Search works because the feasibility is monotonic:

If a path exists with safeness k, then a path also exists for every value < k.


The Max Heap solution works because it is a maximum bottleneck path problem. Like Dijkstra maximizes/minimizes a path metric, here we maximize the minimum safeness seen along the path.



